1
00:01:32,090 --> 00:01:34,940
[How dare you!?]

2
00:01:35,039 --> 00:01:37,940
[Episode 17]

3
00:01:42,110 --> 00:01:43,120
If you don't believe

4
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:45,640
Yu Wanyin would say something like this
to Xie Yong'er,

5
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,370
that's fine.

6
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:51,180
I'll ask you in a different identity.

7
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:56,310
How...

8
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:57,640
Are...

9
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,070
You?

10
00:02:01,030 --> 00:02:01,630
Answer me!

11
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,380
How are you?

12
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,190
You too?

13
00:02:10,710 --> 00:02:11,240
Yes, I am.

14
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:12,630
I'm tired.

15
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,880
Let's put our cards on the table.

16
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:17,820
I don't know what you're talking about.

17
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:19,690
You already know very well who I am.

18
00:02:19,690 --> 00:02:20,490
Stop talking!

19
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:23,190
How long are you going to
keep running from this?

20
00:02:23,190 --> 00:02:24,870
I'll ask you that same question again
right now.

21
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:26,070
Do you dare answer it?

22
00:02:28,030 --> 00:02:28,760
Answer what?

23
00:02:33,030 --> 00:02:33,829
Your Majesty.

24
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,460
Consort Yu has gone crazy.

25
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:37,380
She keeps saying strange things.

26
00:02:37,870 --> 00:02:39,190
I'm really scared.

27
00:02:46,310 --> 00:02:47,000
Is that so?

28
00:02:50,030 --> 00:02:51,360
Let me answer it for you.

29
00:02:56,079 --> 00:02:56,630
Fine.

30
00:02:59,120 --> 00:02:59,840
Thank you.

31
00:03:03,910 --> 00:03:04,870
And you?

32
00:03:07,710 --> 00:03:08,280
You too?

33
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:20,600
[Kunyu Palace]

34
00:03:27,630 --> 00:03:28,560
Why are you here?

35
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:31,000
Is everything with the envoy delegation
settled?

36
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:31,750
More or less.

37
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,960
I muddled through it
without any real trouble.

38
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:36,190
I heard

39
00:03:36,590 --> 00:03:38,850
the Empress Dowager gave you a hard time.

40
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:41,440
I managed to muddle through it as well.

41
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,600
You're awake.

42
00:03:51,150 --> 00:03:52,400
So you two, like me,

43
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:53,910
are also transmigrators?

44
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:54,240
Yes.

45
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,190
Since we're all the same kind...

46
00:03:56,190 --> 00:03:57,850
Since we're all the same kind,

47
00:03:57,910 --> 00:03:59,640
why didn't you tell me earlier?

48
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,240
Did you have to watch me from the shadows

49
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,800
and see me make a fool of myself?

50
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:03,240
Right.

51
00:04:04,910 --> 00:04:07,110
Watching you cheat on me the whole time—

52
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,470
pretty thrilling.

53
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:11,820
Then...

54
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,290
Then why are you telling me now?

55
00:04:14,470 --> 00:04:15,600
Why not just kill me?

56
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:19,040
Just tell the public that Xie Yong'er
died from childbirth complications.

57
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,920
This way, Prince Duan
wouldn't suspect anything.

58
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,270
Wouldn't that be even better?

59
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:22,830
Indeed.

60
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,520
Wanyin, why did you tell her?

61
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:28,040
Well...

62
00:04:28,580 --> 00:04:29,780
Why not just kill her?

63
00:04:35,159 --> 00:04:35,930
Yong'er,

64
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:36,700
look,

65
00:04:37,390 --> 00:04:40,050
we've already reached the point of
miscarriage

66
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,220
and framing each other.

67
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:43,490
If the plot keeps developing like this,

68
00:04:43,490 --> 00:04:45,090
it'll be a fight to the death.

69
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:47,610
Since we're all the same kind,

70
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:50,060
isn't there another possibility for us?

71
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,990
Stop being so hypocritical.

72
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:56,040
You never intended to tell me the truth
from the start.

73
00:04:56,390 --> 00:04:57,390
Now that you see me

74
00:04:57,430 --> 00:04:58,230
in this state,

75
00:04:59,430 --> 00:05:01,480
you come telling me we're the same kind?

76
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:03,740
Haven't you had your fill of the joke yet?

77
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:07,460
If we had told you
right after we transmigrated,

78
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,750
would your first reaction

79
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:10,080
have been to cooperate?

80
00:05:12,070 --> 00:05:14,480
At that time, you had already
sided with Prince Duan.

81
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,880
Suddenly finding out
that I was a wild card,

82
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,950
you'd probably
have gone straight to Prince Duan

83
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:19,610
and told him

84
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:22,490
to take me out

85
00:05:22,630 --> 00:05:23,890
while I was still weak.

86
00:05:24,830 --> 00:05:25,600
Am I wrong?

87
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,360
Makes sense.

88
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:32,110
But

89
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:35,360
is there anything wrong with
me wanting to survive?

90
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,830
Don't you two want to survive?

91
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:38,040
Of course we do.

92
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,250
Yong'er.

93
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:41,390
I don't think you're wrong.

94
00:05:41,390 --> 00:05:43,560
It's this darn situation that's wrong.

95
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,430
If possible,

96
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:46,720
I hope you, me,

97
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:48,430
the three of us

98
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,000
can all make it to the end.

99
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,120
Then we

100
00:05:51,630 --> 00:05:53,030
can have hotpot together

101
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,159
and play a few rounds of
"Fight the Landlord."

102
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:55,420
It would be so much fun.

103
00:05:55,870 --> 00:05:56,930
Stop with your act.

104
00:05:59,950 --> 00:06:01,480
If the roles were reversed,

105
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,530
I believe your choices

106
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:06,180
wouldn't be any different from mine.

107
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:08,840
But the difference is huge.

108
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,390
If Wanyin had been as ruthless

109
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:14,120
as you were when you framed her,

110
00:06:14,510 --> 00:06:16,240
you wouldn't even be alive now.

111
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,510
Come on, bro.

112
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:24,420
Are you determined to sabotage our plan?

113
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,210
That's not the case at all.

114
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,620
Actually, Yong'er

115
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:30,290
is not as cruel as he imagined.

116
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,170
Right, Yong'er?

117
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:37,810
Come on, get up. It's cold on the floor.

118
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:42,010
What are you doing?

119
00:06:42,159 --> 00:06:42,890
I don't think

120
00:06:43,159 --> 00:06:44,750
there's anything more
to talk about with her.

121
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:45,280
Let's go.

122
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:58,480
Why were you constantly
undermining my efforts just now?

123
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,870
Xie Yong'er is emotionally vulnerable
right now.

124
00:07:00,870 --> 00:07:02,200
I was trying to turn her.

125
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:02,830
I know.

126
00:07:03,430 --> 00:07:04,690
I was working with you.

127
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:06,600
What kind of "working with me" is that?

128
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:07,430
I intimidate,

129
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,480
you entice.

130
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:13,070
She cheated on me, all right?

131
00:07:13,070 --> 00:07:15,480
Even if I was just putting on a show
for the Empress Dowager,

132
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:18,210
it's reasonable for me to be
a little harsh on her.

133
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:20,490
Xie Yong'er is a real villain.

134
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,580
Forget about turning her.

135
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:24,360
Do people who've made mistakes

136
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:26,800
not deserve a fresh start?

137
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:33,140
She probably didn't intend to
harm me today.

138
00:07:34,070 --> 00:07:37,000
It was just a stress response to
the Empress Dowager.

139
00:07:37,070 --> 00:07:39,360
I just happened to
have a higher ground than her,

140
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,120
and I met you,

141
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:43,500
which allowed me to seize the initiative

142
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:46,670
and even appear justified
in everything I did.

143
00:07:47,630 --> 00:07:50,090
Everything I did was just
to protect myself.

144
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:52,870
The only reason I wanted her to survive

145
00:07:52,870 --> 00:07:55,870
was because I'm worried
the story would get cut short.

146
00:07:56,830 --> 00:08:00,160
So essentially, I'm not really
any different from her, am I?

147
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:00,940
You are.

148
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,390
Have you never thought

149
00:08:08,270 --> 00:08:09,800
that keeping someone alive

150
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:11,400
can be done in many ways?

151
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,560
Chop off her legs,

152
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:19,650
imprison her for life—

153
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,060
so long as she doesn't die,

154
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,070
the goal

155
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,520
is still achieved, isn't it?

156
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,080
You can't even think of that,

157
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,220
and you dare call yourself a villain?

158
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:35,890
If it were Xie Yong'er,
she'd definitely think of it.

159
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,179
She's just a 2D character.

160
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,320
She's as wicked

161
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:44,100
as the plot requires her to be.

162
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:46,480
You...

163
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,760
What's wrong?

164
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:52,440
Nothing.

165
00:08:57,720 --> 00:09:00,320
Wanyin, you left in a hurry.
Did you eat enough?

166
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:01,910
I'm okay.

167
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,030
I'll just ask the servants

168
00:09:04,030 --> 00:09:06,830
to heat up something
for a late-night snack later.

169
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,540
That's thoughtful of you.

170
00:09:21,630 --> 00:09:23,120
Dealing with the Empress Dowager,

171
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,550
guarding against the Yan State envoys,

172
00:09:24,550 --> 00:09:26,750
and still remembering to bring me food.

173
00:09:35,510 --> 00:09:36,030
No way.

174
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:39,190
Getting moved so easily,

175
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,480
"great villain"?

176
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,460
All right, I'll stop teasing you.

177
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:51,950
Eat up, or I'll have brought it
for nothing.

178
00:09:58,870 --> 00:09:59,600
By the way,

179
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:02,360
what kind of person were you before?

180
00:10:04,190 --> 00:10:05,390
Just an ordinary guy.

181
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,640
No real skills, no connections,

182
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:10,150
and... Okay-looking, I guess.

183
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,010
So modest, huh?

184
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:13,250
What about you?

185
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:14,240
Me?

186
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:16,970
I was also ordinary.

187
00:10:17,270 --> 00:10:18,910
Working nine to five every day,

188
00:10:18,910 --> 00:10:20,840
serving one client after another.

189
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,270
When it got busy,

190
00:10:22,270 --> 00:10:24,400
I didn't even have time to wash my hair—

191
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,930
completely different from how I look now.

192
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,350
No need to put yourself down.

193
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,260
You must have been good-looking as well.

194
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:03,080
Are you alright?

195
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:03,730
I'm fine.

196
00:11:06,270 --> 00:11:06,910
Well,

197
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,960
I'll head back to the palace first.

198
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:13,760
Aren't we still putting on that whole
"chasing-your-wife-after-screwing-up" act?

199
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:16,640
Get some rest early.

200
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:39,600
As soon as the banquet ended,

201
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:42,080
His Majesty immediately
went to Consort Xie's place

202
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:44,390
and tightened the security
around her chambers.

203
00:11:44,390 --> 00:11:45,450
From what I can see,

204
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:48,240
His Majesty is quite attentive to her.

205
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:50,840
It doesn't look like he was
the one behind this.

206
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,130
Then this

207
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,270
really is suspicious.

208
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,240
Could it be

209
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,510
that I overthought it?

210
00:12:02,150 --> 00:12:03,150
You may leave now.

211
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:04,510
Yes.

212
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:10,880
Your Majesty.

213
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:13,440
His Majesty has always kept out of
state affairs.

214
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,480
Why is it that this time, he repeatedly

215
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:16,670
stepped in to smooth things over
for the envoy delegation?

216
00:12:16,670 --> 00:12:17,240
We

217
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:19,600
truly cannot make sense of it.

218
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,790
It seems His Majesty's wings
have grown stronger

219
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:25,920
and he's begun to form ideas of his own.

220
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,660
If the peace talks succeed

221
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:30,750
and the borders are secured,

222
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:32,790
Prince Duan's power

223
00:12:32,790 --> 00:12:34,120
will swell completely,

224
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,530
and we'll be left on the back foot.

225
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,010
So what do you suggest?

226
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,700
His Highness Crown Prince

227
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,870
is wise and benevolent,

228
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:49,360
and he carries the bearing of
a wise ruler.

229
00:13:00,510 --> 00:13:02,240
These Yan people can't even

230
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:06,960
manage a proper sentence
in the official tongue.

231
00:13:07,910 --> 00:13:09,750
Walking around the capital,

232
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:13,390
frictions with the Xia people
are bound to happen.

233
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:15,960
A bunch of barbarians—

234
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,910
one wrong word

235
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:21,910
and they might start throwing punches.

236
00:13:23,390 --> 00:13:24,960
Blades have no eyes.

237
00:13:25,550 --> 00:13:26,610
Before you know it,

238
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,030
there could be bloodshed.

239
00:13:30,390 --> 00:13:31,830
I'll see to it right away.

240
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:37,280
Your Majesty.

241
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:40,000
Killing envoys during a conflict
between two states

242
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,730
could very well spark a new war.

243
00:13:42,270 --> 00:13:43,870
That's right, Your Majesty.

244
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,940
The safety of our state

245
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:49,320
is something we officials
cannot afford not to consider.

246
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:51,000
What's there to worry about?

247
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,670
Even if the Central Army is defeated,

248
00:13:52,670 --> 00:13:55,200
we can still deploy
the Left and Right Armies.

249
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,270
Then we can just sit back and

250
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:59,850
watch the Yan people and Prince Duan
wear each other out.

251
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:00,360
But...

252
00:14:03,670 --> 00:14:04,470
Crown Prince.

253
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,850
What's your take on this?

254
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:12,270
If Grandmother believes we should fight,

255
00:14:12,270 --> 00:14:13,470
then we should fight.

256
00:14:19,790 --> 00:14:20,320
Exactly!

257
00:14:21,510 --> 00:14:23,270
If the Crown Prince says
we fight,

258
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:24,300
then we fight!

259
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:28,480
Thanks to you, Yang,

260
00:14:28,510 --> 00:14:30,000
that I get to enjoy such fine wine today.

261
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,480
I won't stand on ceremony then.

262
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:31,940
Come on.

263
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:34,480
It's rare to see you
drinking so heartily, Li.

264
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,280
I'll join you.

265
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,000
It's been ages since the three of us
got together.

266
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,000
Why are you drinking tea?

267
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:38,860
Switch to wine.

268
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:40,440
I'll pass.

269
00:14:40,790 --> 00:14:43,650
I'd like to stay alive a bit longer
to tend my fields.

270
00:14:45,390 --> 00:14:46,750
Don't drink alone.
Come on, let's drink together.

271
00:14:46,750 --> 00:14:47,680
Come on. Cheers.

272
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:55,240
Yang, since you got here,

273
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:57,000
you've barely said a few words.

274
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:59,000
Aren't you usually the chattiest one?

275
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,060
Why so quiet today?

276
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:03,840
You seem to have lost weight, Yang.

277
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,640
Has something happened?

278
00:15:08,870 --> 00:15:11,670
I never want to talk again
in this lifetime.

279
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:17,840
You two

280
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:19,990
both got what you wished for—

281
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:22,790
you joined the Ministry of Revenue,

282
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,120
and you get to keep studying farming.

283
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:29,670
Do you know what I'm in charge of

284
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:32,070
after entering the Imperial Observatory?

285
00:15:33,270 --> 00:15:34,360
Divination.

286
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,790
Reading the stars for omens of
fortune and disaster, rise and fall.

287
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:42,630
I spend my days spinning stories
for people.

288
00:15:45,910 --> 00:15:47,910
And you think I can just make them up?

289
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,510
No.

290
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:55,630
If His Majesty wants this reading
to foretell misfortune,

291
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,840
then I have to couch it
in grand, arcane phrasing—

292
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:01,240
pacing the constellations,
plumbing the mysteries of change—

293
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:04,600
so that even bad news
sounds ornate and eloquent.

294
00:16:06,870 --> 00:16:09,600
Is my literary talent
really meant for this?

295
00:16:22,390 --> 00:16:23,250
Let them leave.

296
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,620
Enough with the dance.

297
00:16:24,910 --> 00:16:25,370
You all,

298
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:26,240
get out.

299
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:28,090
Get out.

300
00:16:28,790 --> 00:16:30,050
All of you, get out too.

301
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,080
-Let's go then.
-Let's go.

302
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:32,610
Hurry up.

303
00:16:33,870 --> 00:16:35,800
What kind of rubbish dance is that?

304
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:38,760
Nowhere near as good as
the dances of our Great Yan.

305
00:16:39,150 --> 00:16:40,320
And this wine and these dishes—

306
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:41,170
too delicate.

307
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:42,980
Not satisfying at all!

308
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:44,670
Ever since we came to Great Xia,

309
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:46,080
I haven't felt at ease for a single day!

310
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,360
At the Grand Longevity Banquet,

311
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:49,910
the Empress Dowager
was clearly targeting us.

312
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:50,600
I just can't

313
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,320
swallow such insult!

314
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:53,360
Enough.

315
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:57,330
We've long known

316
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:00,730
how insidious and cunning
the Xia people are.

317
00:17:01,550 --> 00:17:03,010
What's most important now

318
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,240
is keeping our composure

319
00:17:05,790 --> 00:17:07,650
and waiting for the right moment.

320
00:17:08,109 --> 00:17:10,569
As long as Xiahou Dan agrees to
meet us alone,

321
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:13,119
we can kill this dog of an emperor

322
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:16,020
without losing a single soldier.

323
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,200
That old Emperor of Yan

324
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:23,069
is counting his chickens too early.

325
00:17:23,069 --> 00:17:24,359
Let's put in some effort

326
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:26,220
and make sure he spends his old age

327
00:17:26,790 --> 00:17:29,120
thoroughly engulfed in the flames of war.

328
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,020
Speaking of which,

329
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,860
we pulled a switcheroo

330
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:36,620
and took
the real envoy delegation's place.

331
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:38,140
Do you think

332
00:17:39,030 --> 00:17:40,410
Zhaluowahan

333
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:42,510
has realized by now?

334
00:17:43,030 --> 00:17:44,070
And what if he has?

335
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:45,680
He's nothing but

336
00:17:46,110 --> 00:17:47,580
a toothless old wolf now.

337
00:17:48,830 --> 00:17:52,540
He's probably eagerly waiting for
the outcome of the peace talks.

338
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:56,490
Alright.

339
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:58,400
Come on.

340
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:58,750
Cheers.

341
00:17:58,750 --> 00:17:59,280
Alright.

342
00:17:59,830 --> 00:18:01,520
It's time for the Xia people

343
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:04,000
to pay the blood debt they owe us.

344
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:05,880
I, Yang Duojie,

345
00:18:06,750 --> 00:18:10,680
with my ten years of diligent study
and exceptional talent,

346
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:13,280
actually ended up
becoming a fortune-teller.

347
00:18:13,790 --> 00:18:15,050
Keep your voices down.

348
00:18:16,550 --> 00:18:16,960
Yang.

349
00:18:20,590 --> 00:18:21,240
Yang.

350
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:23,310
Didn't His Majesty say

351
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:24,720
that, for now, he needs you to write

352
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:27,160
those mystical, mumbo-jumbo pieces
to fool people,

353
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:29,820
and he'll transfer you elsewhere
after a while?

354
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:35,320
Allow me to say something
downright treasonous—

355
00:18:36,110 --> 00:18:37,240
do you believe that?

356
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:38,480
I do.

357
00:18:39,830 --> 00:18:40,760
I believe it too.

358
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:43,200
Therefore,

359
00:18:44,110 --> 00:18:45,270
you should also have

360
00:18:45,830 --> 00:18:47,270
more faith in His Majesty.

361
00:18:47,270 --> 00:18:48,310
His Majesty also told me

362
00:18:48,310 --> 00:18:51,480
to keep compiling the land registers
from various regions,

363
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:53,070
saying they would be useful someday.

364
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:55,870
That counts as the Emperor's promise,
doesn't it?

365
00:18:56,480 --> 00:19:00,410
That's not what you said when you
first joined the Ministry of Revenue.

366
00:19:00,940 --> 00:19:04,130
So you don't mind
Er Lan being so socially adept

367
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:06,070
and rising through the ranks with ease
anymore?

368
00:19:06,070 --> 00:19:07,600
I don't see him that way now.

369
00:19:08,830 --> 00:19:11,510
Then why didn't you invite Er
along today?

370
00:19:12,070 --> 00:19:13,830
You're the host—
shouldn't you be the one to invite him?

371
00:19:13,830 --> 00:19:15,480
But you both work in
the Ministry of Revenue.

372
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:16,920
Yes, we do.

373
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:18,510
I even nodded to him
when I saw him earlier.

374
00:19:18,510 --> 00:19:20,170
I thought he was heading here.

375
00:19:20,510 --> 00:19:21,640
That's on you.

376
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:24,830
Besides, he's probably swamped with
work now. Able men are always busy, right?

377
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:28,290
How would he have time to come out
for our little get-together?

378
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,930
Well said—"able men are always busy."

379
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:35,030
You're all so steadfast.

380
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:39,200
Turns out I'm the only one still wavering.

381
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:46,320
Take Wang Zhao for instance.

382
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:49,510
He was supposed to return
with the envoy delegation,

383
00:19:49,510 --> 00:19:51,440
yet now he's been kept in Yan State.

384
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:55,350
I fear the worst for him.

385
00:19:57,160 --> 00:20:00,030
And His Majesty, fully aware that
the Yan people came with ill intent,

386
00:20:00,030 --> 00:20:02,690
still lowered himself
to curry favor with them.

387
00:20:03,270 --> 00:20:06,110
I can't understand
what he's really thinking,

388
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:07,790
and I don't know

389
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:09,350
-what he takes us for...
-Stop there!

390
00:20:09,350 --> 00:20:10,440
-What's happening?
-What do you want?

391
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:11,310
They're from the Yan State, right?

392
00:20:11,310 --> 00:20:14,270
-You haven't paid yet. You can't leave.
-Looks like it's those Yan fellows.

393
00:20:14,270 --> 00:20:15,750
Speak of the devil.

394
00:20:16,230 --> 00:20:17,890
Six dishes, four jugs of wine—

395
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:20,440
you even gave us two coins in change.

396
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:23,650
That only covers the food and drinks.

397
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:25,800
You didn't pay for the songstress.

398
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,160
What songstress?

399
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:29,340
She came in and sang on her own,

400
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:31,120
and she barely sang a couple of lines

401
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:32,400
before we sent her away.

402
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:33,530
Everyone knows that

403
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:36,390
Miss Miaoying is a star on our street.

404
00:20:36,830 --> 00:20:39,350
So many people spend a fortune
to hire her, yet can't.

405
00:20:39,350 --> 00:20:41,430
How is it that with you Yan folks,

406
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,730
she came performing for you on her own?

407
00:20:51,610 --> 00:20:52,740
How much do you want?

408
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:54,680
You're quite straightforward.

409
00:20:54,790 --> 00:20:55,450
50 taels.

410
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:59,680
They're deliberately giving us trouble.

411
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:01,020
We can't pay this money.

412
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:05,290
Don't forget the purpose of this trip.

413
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:08,130
We can't risk the big picture
over small matters.

414
00:21:12,350 --> 00:21:13,440
That should be enough.

415
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:14,370
It's not enough!

416
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,110
This isn't just a matter of money!

417
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:21,200
They... They even tried to
take advantage of me.

418
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,310
That's pure slander!

419
00:21:22,310 --> 00:21:23,920
Who tried to take advantage of you?

420
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,270
Him! It was him!

421
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:25,680
Me?

422
00:21:25,830 --> 00:21:26,690
Yes, it was him!

423
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:27,650
Everyone, look!

424
00:21:27,750 --> 00:21:28,720
He even left his handprint right here!

425
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:30,160
-You don't think this situation...
-I didn't take advantage of her!

426
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:31,440
Is going to escalate into a fight, do you?

427
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:32,830
Don't jinx it. Just stop talking.

428
00:21:32,830 --> 00:21:33,430
It was him!

429
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:35,720
-How could you hit her?
-Let's go.

430
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:36,920
How could you do that?

431
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:37,620
Stop there!

432
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:44,680
Brother, they're the ones who bullied me!

433
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:46,080
You bullied my sister

434
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,160
and think you can just walk away?

435
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:48,760
Beat them!

436
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,060
We can't kill them.

437
00:21:58,310 --> 00:21:58,920
But, Your Highness...

438
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:00,640
If we kill them, we'll be charged

439
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:01,440
and arrested.

440
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,790
Something's not right.

441
00:22:07,790 --> 00:22:09,200
These people's fighting skills

442
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:11,750
don't seem like those of
ordinary laborers or commoners.

443
00:22:11,750 --> 00:22:12,480
You go first.

444
00:22:12,790 --> 00:22:13,880
We'll stay here and deal with them.

445
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:14,310
No.

446
00:22:15,510 --> 00:22:16,840
We must leave together.

447
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:31,160
Who was it?

448
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:31,820
[Zuixiang House]

449
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:32,700
Run!

450
00:22:34,750 --> 00:22:35,120
Run!

451
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:37,330
Are you crazy?

452
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:39,530
Do you know how much
that jug of wine is worth?

453
00:22:39,530 --> 00:22:40,510
You're the crazy one!

454
00:22:40,510 --> 00:22:41,720
At this point, you still care about money?

455
00:22:41,720 --> 00:22:43,000
Stop arguing, you two.

456
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:44,840
They clearly came prepared.

457
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:47,000
Who knows
if they're the Empress Dowager's people.

458
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,030
Here's what we'll do. Yang,

459
00:22:48,030 --> 00:22:50,270
hurry into the palace
and report this to His Majesty.

460
00:22:50,270 --> 00:22:51,480
Li, let's follow them

461
00:22:51,550 --> 00:22:52,880
and see if we can help.

462
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:54,560
Follow them? I just hit them.

463
00:22:54,750 --> 00:22:56,510
They don't know it was you.

464
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:57,680
Besides,

465
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:59,960
the envoy delegation's safety
is crucial to stopping the war.

466
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:00,820
Let's split up.

467
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:01,750
You're right.

468
00:23:01,750 --> 00:23:02,240
Yang!

469
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:04,210
This way.

470
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:06,990
Do we have to sneak around like thieves?

471
00:23:08,550 --> 00:23:09,070
Stop!

472
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:11,060
Stop there!

473
00:23:13,510 --> 00:23:14,270
Block them!

474
00:23:24,710 --> 00:23:26,440
There's a path behind the wall.

475
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:27,400
Climb over!

476
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:27,850
Okay.

477
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:38,410
Let's go!

478
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:43,130
Stop! Don't run!

479
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:44,800
Get down here!

480
00:23:47,830 --> 00:23:48,110
Easy!

481
00:23:48,110 --> 00:23:49,110
Behave yourself!

482
00:23:50,750 --> 00:23:51,130
Move!

483
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:02,880
Thank you for the timely report, Mr. Li.

484
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:06,210
We'll take these criminals back
for thorough questioning.

485
00:24:10,310 --> 00:24:12,030
Those Yan State envoys

486
00:24:12,790 --> 00:24:14,190
should have left safely.

487
00:24:16,030 --> 00:24:17,710
They actually dared carry out

488
00:24:17,830 --> 00:24:19,750
such bandit-like attacks
in broad daylight.

489
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:20,240
It seems

490
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,750
the Empress Dowager is really going to
show her real colors.

491
00:24:22,750 --> 00:24:24,480
The crisis in these peace talks

492
00:24:24,750 --> 00:24:25,950
is still unresolved.

493
00:24:27,550 --> 00:24:30,410
Let's hope His Majesty
can make preparations soon.

494
00:24:37,510 --> 00:24:38,440
Where's Hawugu?

495
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,110
Those people who came to kill us

496
00:24:47,110 --> 00:24:49,510
must have been sent by
the Empress Dowager.

497
00:24:50,110 --> 00:24:52,570
That woman targeted me
back in the main hall.

498
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:54,720
I suppose she couldn't think of
any other tricks.

499
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,830
Those soldiers arrived pretty fast though.

500
00:24:56,830 --> 00:24:58,680
It was probably the person
who threw the jug

501
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,200
who notified the soldiers.

502
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,860
Could it be the Emperor's men?

503
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:03,140
Not likely.

504
00:25:03,750 --> 00:25:04,480
I don't think

505
00:25:05,510 --> 00:25:06,540
they're with the same group as

506
00:25:06,540 --> 00:25:08,870
the ones who told us to
climb over the wall.

507
00:25:09,270 --> 00:25:12,070
So there's internal conflict in Great Xia
as well.

508
00:25:13,550 --> 00:25:14,080
Let's go.

509
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:21,700
I left right after giving the signal.

510
00:25:21,830 --> 00:25:23,160
As Your Highness instructed,

511
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:26,160
I didn't show my face in front of
the envoy delegation.

512
00:25:26,830 --> 00:25:28,440
Did you discover anything else?

513
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:30,040
That Haqina in their group

514
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:33,160
doesn't seem to be the real leader.

515
00:25:34,270 --> 00:25:35,270
During the fight,

516
00:25:35,790 --> 00:25:38,850
I heard him call that burly attendant
"Your Highness."

517
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:42,820
I also found that bearded man
very suspicious.

518
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:45,640
He seemed to be deliberately disguised,

519
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:48,030
and he kept reminding those around him

520
00:25:48,050 --> 00:25:49,510
not to provoke conflicts.

521
00:25:50,510 --> 00:25:51,370
I remember now.

522
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,930
There was indeed such a person.

523
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:57,200
At the Grand Longevity Banquet,

524
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:58,850
you said he was a master fighter,
right, Mr. Bei?

525
00:25:58,850 --> 00:25:59,650
That's right.

526
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:01,640
That man's internal force
is extremely profound,

527
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:03,100
far superior to Haqina's.

528
00:26:03,720 --> 00:26:05,050
So here's the question:

529
00:26:06,350 --> 00:26:07,810
why would a master fighter

530
00:26:08,420 --> 00:26:10,350
disguise himself as an attendant?

531
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:11,830
Those Yan people

532
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,000
have probably never

533
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:16,730
been truly seen by
our Great Xia's people before.

534
00:26:17,350 --> 00:26:20,610
There's supposed to be no need for them
to hide their faces.

535
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:22,080
Since he's in disguise,

536
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:24,690
he must be someone familiar to us.

537
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:28,400
The occasion where our people
would recognize his face...

538
00:26:29,590 --> 00:26:30,920
Could it be...

539
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:32,960
The battlefield?

540
00:26:33,270 --> 00:26:34,310
With his skills,

541
00:26:35,350 --> 00:26:39,010
he could indeed live up to the title of
top fighter of the Yan State.

542
00:26:39,270 --> 00:26:40,200
He's Tu'er!

543
00:26:40,730 --> 00:26:43,650
[Prince Tu'er]

544
00:26:41,190 --> 00:26:43,630
With the beard, they do look

545
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:45,680
about 70% to 80% similar.

546
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:47,400
But it's long been rumored that

547
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:49,350
Tu'er and the old Emperor of Yan
are at odds.

548
00:26:49,350 --> 00:26:51,880
So how could he have been sent
as part of the envoy delegation?

549
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:52,680
Could it be...

550
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:54,030
The envoy delegation is fake.

551
00:26:54,030 --> 00:26:54,960
No wonder!

552
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:57,480
No wonder Wang Zhao
didn't come back with them.

553
00:26:57,480 --> 00:26:58,280
Your Majesty,

554
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:01,030
they must be carrying many schemes
on this visit.

555
00:27:01,030 --> 00:27:03,290
Please be extra cautious, Your Majesty.

556
00:27:03,590 --> 00:27:04,390
I understand.

557
00:27:08,270 --> 00:27:09,400
Here's what we'll do.

558
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:09,930
Mr. Yang.

559
00:27:10,030 --> 00:27:10,680
Yes, Your Majesty.

560
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:14,310
Send the Ministry of Rites to
the envoy delegation's inn to apologize.

561
00:27:14,310 --> 00:27:15,590
The more ceremonious the display,
the better.

562
00:27:15,590 --> 00:27:16,250
Apologize?

563
00:27:16,790 --> 00:27:17,920
But shouldn't we...

564
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:22,500
Yes, Your Majesty.

565
00:27:27,510 --> 00:27:28,000
Dan.

566
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:30,510
Those Yan people have not come
with good intentions.

567
00:27:30,510 --> 00:27:32,570
You should make preparations early.

568
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:34,460
If we want peace talks,

569
00:27:35,070 --> 00:27:36,270
we have to take risks.

570
00:27:37,790 --> 00:27:38,880
Besides, in a way,

571
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:42,160
Tu'er and I should have met long ago.

572
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:43,380
Then should we

573
00:27:43,790 --> 00:27:45,520
tell Wanyin about this matter?

574
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:46,000
No.

575
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:50,210
The matter with Xie Yong'er

576
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:52,240
is already troubling her enough.

577
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:54,440
I don't want to add more pressure on her.

578
00:27:56,030 --> 00:27:57,150
[Prince Tu'er]

579
00:27:57,150 --> 00:28:01,430
[Beautiful Lady Shanyi]

580
00:28:02,340 --> 00:28:05,300
[A few years ago]

581
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:41,340
[Yixuan Restaurant]

582
00:28:46,550 --> 00:28:48,950
This is a gift sent by
the Great Xia Emperor,

583
00:28:50,270 --> 00:28:52,110
saying it's compensation
to our envoy delegation

584
00:28:52,110 --> 00:28:53,970
for what happened during the day.

585
00:28:56,550 --> 00:28:58,040
All they know

586
00:28:58,590 --> 00:28:59,720
is how to apologize.

587
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,550
I noticed there are more guards
on duty today.

588
00:29:04,110 --> 00:29:06,440
It's said they were specially reinforced

589
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:08,920
to prevent the criminals
from striking again—

590
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:10,120
to protect us.

591
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:13,810
Whether they're trying to protect us

592
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:15,570
or keep an eye on us

593
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:17,510
is hard to say.

594
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:21,530
You know, years ago,

595
00:29:22,070 --> 00:29:24,680
when the Emperor of Yan
fought against our country,

596
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:26,600
he didn't just get shot in one eye—

597
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:29,510
he was actually hit in another part
of his body as well.

598
00:29:29,510 --> 00:29:31,850
That's why he has no children of his own

599
00:29:32,070 --> 00:29:34,050
and only has Tu'er as his nephew.

600
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:38,120
Zhaluowahan may not have been
especially close to Tu'er,

601
00:29:38,550 --> 00:29:41,480
but he dutifully taught him
how to ride and hunt.

602
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:43,740
Who would have thought

603
00:29:44,070 --> 00:29:46,800
those two had such affection
as uncle and nephew?

604
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:50,920
In the blink of an eye,
Tu'er grew into a valiant young man,

605
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:53,550
surpassing the Emperor of Yan
in riding and archery,

606
00:29:53,550 --> 00:29:56,880
and the number of subjects supporting him
gradually increased.

607
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:59,530
As Tu'er became the Yan State's
top fighter,

608
00:29:59,790 --> 00:30:01,310
calls for the old Emperor of Yan
to abdicate

609
00:30:01,310 --> 00:30:02,840
and give the throne to Tu'er

610
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:04,680
grew louder by the day.

611
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:11,380
Truly, raising a nephew
turned out to be the uncle's hardship.

612
00:30:13,790 --> 00:30:16,750
Beautiful Lady Shanyi
was originally Tu'er's lover,

613
00:30:16,750 --> 00:30:19,750
but was sent to Great Xia
as a gift by the Emperor of Yan.

614
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:23,000
She later died in the palace
after a failed assassination attempt.

615
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,750
However, afterward, the Yan people

616
00:30:24,750 --> 00:30:26,680
not only denied the assassination attempt,

617
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,940
but even accused Great Xia of killing her

618
00:30:29,270 --> 00:30:32,000
and used this as an excuse
to wage war against us.

619
00:30:32,750 --> 00:30:36,300
So Tu'er must hate the Emperor to death.

620
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:37,270
This time,

621
00:30:38,030 --> 00:30:40,460
could he be trying to imitate Jing Ke,

622
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:44,240
changing his name and disguising himself
to infiltrate the envoy delegation?

623
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:45,960
Risking his life seems unnecessary.

624
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:48,160
The Emperor is already in a weak position,

625
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:50,060
and the expert by his side is dead.

626
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:54,620
And this time, Tu'er has brought
a whole group of Jing Kes with him.

627
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:56,740
Your Highness,

628
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,680
do you think we should

629
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:01,160
reveal something to the Emperor?

630
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:07,550
I didn't expect that you, Mr. Cao,

631
00:31:07,550 --> 00:31:09,810
would be so concerned about the Emperor.

632
00:31:09,930 --> 00:31:12,940
I'm thinking entirely of
Your Highness's interests.

633
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:16,180
If Tu'er really kills the Emperor,

634
00:31:16,270 --> 00:31:17,880
war will break out
between our states again.

635
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:18,720
By then,

636
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:22,080
we won't have resources
to deal with the Empress Dowager.

637
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:24,530
I was thinking the same thing earlier.

638
00:31:26,350 --> 00:31:28,080
But then I realized something.

639
00:31:28,350 --> 00:31:30,210
Since the person coming is Tu'er,

640
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:31,850
with his skills,

641
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:33,960
when carrying out the assassin
like Jing Ke,

642
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:36,560
accidentally killing
the Empress Dowager too

643
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:39,820
shouldn't be difficult, right?

644
00:31:40,410 --> 00:31:42,790
With no one at the helm,

645
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:44,820
formidable enemies outside,

646
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:46,680
and the Crown Prince still young,

647
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:50,640
someone would have to serve as regent
to manage state affairs.

648
00:31:50,830 --> 00:31:51,710
As for the war,

649
00:31:52,030 --> 00:31:53,760
since we're all aware of it now,

650
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:55,380
we can prepare in advance,

651
00:31:55,510 --> 00:31:57,350
so we won't be caught off guard

652
00:31:57,590 --> 00:31:59,590
by the Yan State's surprise attack.

653
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:02,320
Therefore, we need not inform the Emperor.

654
00:32:03,910 --> 00:32:05,160
When necessary,

655
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:08,990
we can even lend Tu'er a helping hand.

656
00:32:29,030 --> 00:32:30,860
[Ten years ago] [Emperor of Yan]

657
00:32:30,910 --> 00:32:33,140
[Ten years ago]

658
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,800
Your Majesty, this is Tu'er.

659
00:32:34,510 --> 00:32:35,550
Un... Un...

660
00:32:36,510 --> 00:32:37,380
Uncle.

661
00:32:47,510 --> 00:32:48,240
Does it hurt?

662
00:32:48,770 --> 00:32:49,630
No, it doesn't.

663
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:56,650
What's this?

664
00:32:57,270 --> 00:32:58,670
It's a Camel Bell flower.

665
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,130
It's really pretty.

666
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:30,190
Shanyi!

667
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:34,210
Is it pretty?

668
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:36,840
Yes, it is.

669
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,920
I'm about to leave for the Great Xia.

670
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,660
Has our Yan State run out of men

671
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:47,130
that we have to send a woman
as an envoy?

672
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:49,350
Because I'm the holy maiden

673
00:33:49,350 --> 00:33:50,880
chosen by the people of Yan.

674
00:33:51,350 --> 00:33:53,980
Naturally, I must go and dance for them.

675
00:33:55,030 --> 00:33:57,110
This is a dagger I made myself.

676
00:33:57,880 --> 00:33:59,210
Take it for protection.

677
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:02,330
It's really pretty.

678
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:05,600
Even engraved with Camel Bell flowers.

679
00:34:07,350 --> 00:34:09,020
I wanted to go with you,

680
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:12,570
but Uncle insists I stay
to handle state affairs.

681
00:34:13,710 --> 00:34:15,510
Please be extra careful on your journey.

682
00:34:15,510 --> 00:34:16,250
Don't worry.

683
00:34:16,510 --> 00:34:18,510
I'm going for peace talks, not war.

684
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:20,340
There won't be any danger.

685
00:34:20,630 --> 00:34:23,090
Shanyi, hurry up!
We're all waiting for you.

686
00:34:23,150 --> 00:34:23,610
Coming!

687
00:34:30,630 --> 00:34:31,170
Tu'er.

688
00:34:31,710 --> 00:34:33,000
Wait for me to come back.

689
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,600
I have something to tell you.

690
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:39,239
Uncle.

691
00:34:39,630 --> 00:34:41,230
Why hasn't Shanyi returned?

692
00:34:41,590 --> 00:34:42,850
She's the holy maiden.

693
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:45,810
She should have returned with
the envoy delegation.

694
00:34:54,550 --> 00:34:55,070
Uncle.

695
00:34:57,510 --> 00:34:58,910
What happened to Shanyi?

696
00:34:59,480 --> 00:35:01,280
That Emperor of the Great Xia...

697
00:35:02,190 --> 00:35:04,250
He was impressed by Shanyi's dancing

698
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:07,000
and actually tried to
take advantage of her

699
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,600
right there in the main hall!

700
00:35:09,230 --> 00:35:09,880
Shanyi

701
00:35:11,250 --> 00:35:12,650
refused to be humiliated

702
00:35:12,900 --> 00:35:14,150
and fought back fiercely,

703
00:35:14,150 --> 00:35:15,510
but that Emperor...

704
00:35:17,030 --> 00:35:20,290
He actually killed Shanyi!

705
00:35:38,800 --> 00:35:40,940
Zhang San's Diary.

706
00:36:20,100 --> 00:36:23,850
[Rockery]

707
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:25,870
[1-3 AM]

708
00:36:25,950 --> 00:36:33,710
[Rockery]

709
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:29,400
It's her.

710
00:36:31,670 --> 00:36:32,430
She's here.

711
00:36:33,810 --> 00:36:36,030
[1-3 AM]
